he maximum of the current interval's end and the last interval's end.\n   - If it doesn't overlap, add the current interval to `merged`.\n\n### Edge Cases\n\n- **Empty List**: If the input list is empty, return an empty list.\n- **Single Interval**: If there is only one interval, return that interval as is.\n- **Non-overlapping Intervals**: If all intervals are non-overlapping, simply return the list as is.\n\n### Complexity\n\n- **Time Complexity**: The sorting step takes \\(O(n \\"}
